  ##If you're coming to work in an eligible skilled job

  You may be eligible for the [Skilled Worker visa](https://www.gov.uk/skilled-worker-visa).

  ###Eligibility

  The eligibility criteria include:

  - working in an eligible job - various jobs in research and academia are eligible
  - having a job offer
  - being paid a minimum salary - how much depends on the type of work you do
  - usually proving that you can read, write, speak and understand English

  ###How long you can stay

  Your visa can last for up to 5 years. You can extend it as long as you're still eligible.

  After 5 years, you may be able to apply to settle permanently in the UK.

  ----

  ##If you’re a leader or potential leader in your field

  You may be eligible for the [Global Talent visa](https://www.gov.uk/global-talent-researcher-academic) if you are a leader or potential leader in science, medicine, engineering or humanities.

  With this visa, you:

  + may be able to work in the UK without a job offer
  + can be an employee, self-employed and a director of a company

  ###Eligibility

  The eligibility criteria include proving you are a leader or potential leader in your field by applying for an ‘endorsement’.

  There are no English language or minimum salary eligibility requirements.

  ###How long you can stay

  Your visa can last for up to 5 years.  You can extend it as long as you're still eligible.

  After 3 years, you may be able to settle permanently in the UK.

  ----

  ##If you’re coming to work in a research or training programme

  You may be eligible for a [Temporary Worker - Government Authorised Exchange visa (T5)](https://www.gov.uk/government-authorised-exchange).

  You can work as a researcher, visiting academic or examiner if it’s part of an approved programme.

  The application fee is cheaper than the Skilled Worker or Global Talent visa.

  ###Eligibility

  The eligibility criteria include having a job offer.

  ###How long you can stay

  You can stay up to 2 years in the UK on this visa. If you want to stay longer you must switch to another type of visa.

